AGI - Morning at the Auditorium of Via della Conciliazione for Pope Francis who spoke before the General States of the birth. A theme, this, very dear to the Pontiff who cares for the increasingly reduced number of births in our country.
&nbsp;
"The number of births - it has explained - is the first indicator of the hope of a people. Without children and young people, a country loses its desire for future. In Italy, for example, the average age is currently forty-seven years, in other countries is 26, and new negative records continue to be marked. Unfortunately, if we were to rely on this, we would have to say that Italy is gradually losing its hope in tomorrow, like the rest of Europe: the Old Continent is increasingly transformed into an old, tired and resigned continent, so committed to exorcizing the solitudes and agonizes them not to be able to taste, in the civilization of gift, the true beauty of life. In the houses, children are left, but dogs and cats are missing. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
For Francis, "human life is not a problem, it is a gift. And at the base of pollution and hunger in the world there are no children born, but the choices of those who think only of themselves, the delirium of an unbridled, blind and rampant materialism, of a consumerism that, like a malevolent virus, affects at the root the existence of people and society. They are not the children, but selfishness, which creates injustices and structures of sin, up to interdependence between social, economic and political systems". &nbsp;&nbsp;Bergoglio wanted to remember that the most 'floating' economic sectors are those of weapons and anti-tanks. "One destroys life, the other prevents it from forming."
&nbsp;
<div </div
<br Hence an appeal to governments:&nbsp; "There is a need for greater commitment on the part of all of them, so that young generations are put in the condition of being able to realize their own legitimate dreams. It is a matter of implementing serious and effective choices for the family. For example, to put a mother in the condition of not having to choose between work and care of children; or to free so many young couples from the ballast of occupational precariousness and the impossibility of buying a house".&nbsp; But Bergoglio also appeals to young people: "I know that for many of you the future can look creepy, and that between denatility, wars, pandemics and climate change is not easy to keep hope alive. But don't give up, trust me, because tomorrow is not something ineluctable: We build it together, and in this "together" first we find the Lord. Let's not reassign to a script already written by others, let's row to reverse the course, even at the cost of going countercurrent! As the mothers and the Popes of the Foundation for Christmas do, that every year organize this event, this yard of hope that helps us to think, and that grows, increasingly involving the world of politics, businesses, banks, sports, entertainment and journalism". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;

